"n.白蚁 【考】 pun : joke / termite : insect(双关语是一种笑话/ 白蚁是一种昆虫) n. 白蚁(一种数量巨大、颜色较浅、身体柔软的群居昆虫, 以木材为食, 经常破坏树木和木制的物品) 【记】读: 透明体－透明的蚂蚁－白蚁 【类】pun: joke = termite: insect双关语是一种笑话 = 白蚁是一种昆虫 【记】ter 土地的字根 + mite 螨虫→土里的螨虫→白蚁；音:土埋的，土里埋着的白蚁 termite (n.)  1849, back-formation from plural form termites (1781), from Modern Latin termites (three syllables), plural of termes (genitive termitis), a special use of Late Latin termes ""woodworm, white ant,"" altered (by influence of Latin terere ""to rub, wear, erode"") from earlier Latin tarmes. Their nest is a terminarium (1863). Earlier in English known as wood ant or white ant."
